As a Nigerian, I would choose option 2 because in our culture, religion is deeply important, but it's not just about following rituals. We strongly emphasize the practical demonstration of faith through acts of kindness, community support, and helping others. Many Nigerians, whether Christian or Muslim, believe that true religious practice is reflected in how we treat our fellow human beings with compassion, respect, and generosity. Doing good to others is seen as a fundamental expression of religious devotion, not just adherence to formal ceremonies.
